com.qualcomm.toq.smartwatch.api.v1.deckofcards
Class DeckOfCards

java.lang.Object
  com.qualcomm.toq.smartwatch.api.v1.deckofcards.DeckOfCards
All Implemented Interfaces:
Parcelable
Direct Known Subclasses:
RemoteDeckOfCards
public class DeckOfCards
extends Object
implements Parcelable

An abstract representation of a deck of cards, which is the peer to a deck of cards applet on the Toq smartwatch.

A deck of cards consists of a ListCard which contains one or more Cards. On the Toq smartwatch, this structure is represented as an applet icon which launches a scrollable panel of card summaries, with each summary linking to an individual card.

Optionally, custom launcher icons can be defined which are used instead of the default launcher icons.

A specialised RemoteDeckOfCards implementation exists for use with the Toq app's API service.

Author:
mcaunter
See Also:
